    that is subject to change without notice and cannot be referred to or relied upon as a final ISO&#xD;
    standard.&lt;/em>&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_D3iaEKZjEeCmzNtTCfivQw" name="Select methods for the level of robustness" guid="_D3iaEKZjEeCmzNtTCfivQw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    To determine the test required to ensure the Level of robustness of the item, please refer to &quot;Table 13-Level of&#xD;
    robustness&quot; located in ISO 26262, volume 4, clause 8.4.3.2.5, in summary the tests to be carried out are&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;blockquote style=&quot;MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Resource usage test (this test is recommended for ASIL B and highly recommended for ASILs C and D)&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Stress test (this test is recommended for ASIL B and highly recommended for ASILs C and D)&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Test for interference resistance and robustness under certain environmental condition (this test is highly&#xD;
        recommended for all ASILs)&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;/blockquote>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    At the item level, lab cars or prototypes are usually employed to create&amp;nbsp;a dynamic environment for the tests. The&#xD;
    focus of these test are items such as power consumption or bus loading.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Stress tests are used to verify the correct operation of the item under high operational loads or extreme environmental&#xD;
    conditions.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    A test for interference resistance and robustness under certain environmental conditions is a special case of stress&#xD;
    testing. This includes EMC and ESD tests.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br /></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <purpose>&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    To describe the verification tools, methods and environment with pass and fail criteria to be applied at the System&#xD;
    integration level.&#xD;
&lt;/p></purpose>
